Zambia’s Sata Fires Anti-Corruption Chief, Three Senior Aides

-- B y   A n t h o n y   M u k w i t a
-- 
2011-10-02T13:57:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-02/zambia-s-sata-fires-anti-corruption-chief-three-senior-aides.html
Zambia’s newly elected President
 Michael Sata  fired the country’s anti-corruption chief and three
senior aides.  Sata, known to his supporters as “King Cobra” for his
aggressive political style, dismissed Richard Chembe, Joseph
Jalasi and Francis Chigunta, his special assistants for
economic, legal and political affairs, respectively, according
to an e-mailed statement today from Sata’s spokesman, George
Chellah. Godfrey Kayukwa, head of the Anti-Corruption Commission
was sacked yesterday, Chella wrote.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Mukwita in Lusaka via Johannesburg at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net 
